      "message": "Here are the reasons why I decided to introduce separate structs instead of using proto messages:\n1. For consistency with the existing client API that doesn\u0027t expose proto messages (due to historical reasons, the first version of CIPD protocol was not protobuf based). I believe it\u0027s better to keep everything consistent.\n2. `-json-output` in the CLI uses encoding/json and interface{} for serializing stuff. Proto messages are not easily encodable with encoding/json (they require using protobuf-specific JSON serialization library).",
